      • getSamplePeriod

        java.lang.Integer getSamplePeriod()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns:
        the sample period of the time steps. Has to be a divider of time steps. This will specify the resolution of returned partial results. Examples: TimeSteps=500, SamplePeriod=100 => 5 results are returned TimeSteps=500, SamplePeriod=1 => all 500 results returned TimeSteps=500, SamplePeriod=500 => only last result returned
